  "publisher": "dc",
  "about": "Dr. Thomas \"Tommy\" Elliot, better known as Hush, is a supervillain appearing in American comic books published by DC Comics. Created by Jeph Loeb and Jim Lee, the character first appeared in Batman #609 in January 2003 as part of the twelve-issue storyline Batman: Hush. Hush's background is parallel to the superhero Batman, and he serves as a criminal foil to him, as an example of what Batman could have been if he came from an abusive family and had used his abilities and resources for malice. Hush belongs to the collective of adversaries that make up Batman's rogues' gallery. Hush resides in Gotham City.",
  "note": null,
  "source": "dc"
